    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1892-07-12T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1892-07-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="394"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d394">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Foster</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Sagrario</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1892-07-12">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 12, 1892</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to your note of the 27th ultimo, it
                    gives me much pleasure to be able to inform you that the Secretary of the Navy
                    has ordered the commanding officer of the U. S. S. <hi rend="italic"
                        >Bennington</hi> to proceed with that vessel from Montevideo to Palos,
                    Spain, to arrive there by the 1st of August next, and to take part in the
                    celebrations in honor of the sailing of Columbus from that port.</p>
                <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">John W. Foster</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
